hopobject.body: I'll send you a text avenues pharmacy stepney This spending is ingrained and prevalent - 99.5 percent of teachers spend out-of-pocket on school supplies, the NSSEA survey found, and there is even a line item for it on federal income tax forms. Teachers in grades K-12 can claim up to $250 each in unreimbursed expenses. They can claim any amount over that on a separate line, as an unreimbursed employee expense, but they are then subject to the same rules as everyone else - only the amount above 2 percent of adjusted gross income is deductible.
